SIMPLE: singly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Singly
<hw>Sin"gly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Individually; particularly; severally; <as>as, to make men
<ex>singly</ex> and personally good</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Only; by one's self; alone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Look thee, 't is so! Thou <qex>singly</qex> honest man.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Without partners, companions, or associates;
single-handed; <as>as, to attack another <ex>singly</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At omber <qex>singly</qex> to decide their doom.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Honestly; sincerely; simply.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Singularly; peculiarly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sing-sing</ent>⟦br⟧
